cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.MA 

This paper is primarily focused on game theory, specifically the concept of strong Nash equilibrium. Therefore, cs.GT (Game Theory and Economics) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses computational methods for finding SNE, which suggests that it could also be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The spatial branch-and-bound algorithm mentioned in the paper falls under the category of optimization algorithms, which could also place the paper under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems).
